This paper deals with algorithms for finding a minimum independent dominating set in graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which are commonly studied in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The study of graphs and their properties falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the use of algorithms to solve optimization problems is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
